{
  "text": "1.2 Review of (2, 2k + 1) strings and the Kontsevich model Minimal bosonic string theories are specified by a pair (p, q) of relatively prime integers. 5 In the continuum, they are formulated in the usual way by taking the total CFT = CFT (p,q) ⊕ CFT Liouville ⊕ CFT ghost . Here CFT (p,q) is a minimal (p, q) model [CITATION_1] , of central charge",
